Basic barplot

library(ggplot2)

# Create data
data <- data.frame(
  name=c("A","B","C","D","E") ,  
  value=c(3,12,5,18,45)
)

head(data)
##   name value
## 1    A     3
## 2    B    12
## 3    C     5
## 4    D    18
## 5    E    45
# Barplot
ggplot(data, aes(x=name, y=value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity")

Control bar color

# 1: Using Hue
ggplot(mtcars, aes(x=as.factor(cyl), fill=as.factor(cyl) )) + 
  geom_bar( ) + scale_fill_hue(c = 40) + theme(legend.position="none")

# 2: Using RColorBrewer
ggplot(mtcars, aes(x=as.factor(cyl), fill=as.factor(cyl) )) + 
  geom_bar( ) + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + theme(legend.position="none")

# 3: Using greyscale:
ggplot(mtcars, aes(x=as.factor(cyl), fill=as.factor(cyl) )) + 
  geom_bar( ) + scale_fill_grey(start = 0.25, end = 0.75) + theme(legend.position="none")

# 4: Set manualy
ggplot(mtcars, aes(x=as.factor(cyl), fill=as.factor(cyl) )) +  
  geom_bar( ) + scale_fill_manual(values = c("darkred", "darkgreen", "darkblue") ) +
  theme(legend.position="none")

Horizontal barplot

ggplot(data, aes(x=name, y=value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  coord_flip()

Control bar width

ggplot(data, aes(x=name, y=value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width=0.2)

Reorder a variable

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

data <- data.frame(
  name=c("north","south","south-east","north-west","south-west","north-east","west","east"),
  val=sample(seq(1,10), 8 )
)

head(data)
##         name val
## 1      north  10
## 2      south   9
## 3 south-east   3
## 4 north-west   2
## 5 south-west   7
## 6 north-east   4

library(forcats)

data <- data %>% mutate(name = fct_reorder(name, val)) # Reorder 
ggplot(data, aes(x=name, y=val)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="#f68060", alpha=.6, width=.4) +
  coord_flip() + xlab("") + theme_bw()

data <- data %>% mutate(name = fct_reorder(name, desc(val))) # Reverse side
ggplot(data, aes(x=name, y=val)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="#f68060", alpha=.6, width=.4) +
  coord_flip() + xlab("") + theme_bw()

# Reorder following a specific order
data <- data %>% mutate(name = fct_relevel(
  name, "north", "north-east", "east", "south-east", "south", "south-west", "west", "north-west"))
ggplot(data, aes(x=name, y=val)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") + xlab("")

Barplot with variable width

library(ggplot2)
library(hrbrthemes) # for style

# make data
data <- data.frame(
  group=c("A ","B ","C ","D ") , 
  value=c(33,62,56,67) , 
  number_of_obs=c(100,500,459,342)
)
 
# Calculate the future positions on the x axis of each bar (left border, central position, right border)
data$right <- cumsum(data$number_of_obs) + 30*c(0:(nrow(data)-1))
data$left <- data$right - data$number_of_obs 

head(data)
##   group value number_of_obs right left
## 1    A     33           100   100    0
## 2    B     62           500   630  130
## 3    C     56           459  1119  660
## 4    D     67           342  1491 1149

ggplot(data, aes(ymin = 0)) + 
    geom_rect(aes(xmin = left, xmax = right, ymax = value, colour = group, fill = group)) +
    xlab("number of obs") + ylab("value") +
    theme_ipsum() + theme(legend.position="none")

Barplot with error bars

library(ggplot2)

data <- data.frame(
  name=letters[1:5],
  value=sample(seq(4,15),5),
  sd=c(1,0.2,3,2,4)
)

head(data)
##   name value  sd
## 1    a     4 1.0
## 2    b     9 0.2
## 3    c    12 3.0
## 4    d     6 2.0
## 5    e     8 4.0

ggplot(data) +
    geom_bar( aes(x=name, y=value), stat="identity", fill="skyblue", alpha=0.7) +
    geom_errorbar( aes(x=name, ymin=value-sd, ymax=value+sd), 
                   width=0.4, colour="orange", alpha=0.9, size=1.3)

Standard deviation, Standard error, Confidence Interval

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

data <- iris %>% select(Species, Sepal.Length) 
 
my_sum <- data %>%
  group_by(Species) %>%
  summarise( 
    n=n(),
    mean=mean(Sepal.Length),
    sd=sd(Sepal.Length) # Standard deviation
  ) %>%
  mutate( se=sd/sqrt(n))  %>% # Standard error
  mutate( ic=se * qt((1-0.05)/2 + .5, n-1)) # Confidence Interval 

head(my_sum)
## # A tibble: 3 × 6
##   Species        n  mean    sd     se    ic
##   <fct>      <int> <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 setosa        50  5.01 0.352 0.0498 0.100
## 2 versicolor    50  5.94 0.516 0.0730 0.147
## 3 virginica     50  6.59 0.636 0.0899 0.181

# Standard deviation
ggplot(my_sum) +
  geom_bar( aes(x=Species, y=mean), stat="identity", fill="forestgreen", alpha=0.5) +
  geom_errorbar( aes(x=Species, ymin=mean-sd, ymax=mean+sd), 
                 width=0.4, colour="orange", alpha=0.9, size=1.5) +
  ggtitle("using standard deviation")

# Standard Error
ggplot(my_sum) +
  geom_bar( aes(x=Species, y=mean), stat="identity", fill="forestgreen", alpha=0.5) +
  geom_errorbar( aes(x=Species, ymin=mean-se, ymax=mean+se), 
                 width=0.4, colour="orange", alpha=0.9, size=1.5) +
  ggtitle("using standard error")

# Confidence Interval
ggplot(my_sum) +
  geom_bar( aes(x=Species, y=mean), stat="identity", fill="forestgreen", alpha=0.5) +
  geom_errorbar( aes(x=Species, ymin=mean-ic, ymax=mean+ic), 
                 width=0.4, colour="orange", alpha=0.9, size=1.5) +
  ggtitle("using confidence interval")

Grouped barplot

library(ggplot2)
 
specie <- c(rep("sorgho" , 3) , rep("poacee" , 3) , rep("banana" , 3) , rep("triticum" , 3) )
condition <- rep(c("normal" , "stress" , "Nitrogen") , 4)
value <- abs(rnorm(12 , 0 , 15))
data <- data.frame(specie,condition,value)

head(data)
##   specie condition     value
## 1 sorgho    normal 17.144645
## 2 sorgho    stress 32.349692
## 3 sorgho  Nitrogen 15.406155
## 4 poacee    normal 10.542569
## 5 poacee    stress 23.746303
## 6 poacee  Nitrogen  7.489596

ggplot(data, aes(fill=condition, y=value, x=specie)) + 
    geom_bar(position="dodge", stat="identity")

Stacked barplot

ggplot(data, aes(fill=condition, y=value, x=specie)) + 
    geom_bar(position="stack", stat="identity")

Percent stacked barplot

ggplot(data, aes(fill=condition, y=value, x=specie)) + 
    geom_bar(position="fill", stat="identity")

Grouped barplot customization

library(ggplot2)
library(viridis)
library(hrbrthemes)

ggplot(data, aes(x=specie, y=value, fill=condition)) + 
    geom_bar(position="stack", stat="identity") + scale_fill_viridis(discrete = T) +
    ggtitle("Studying 4 species.") + theme_ipsum() + xlab("")

Small multiple

ggplot(data, aes(fill=condition, y=value, x=condition)) + 
    geom_bar(position="dodge", stat="identity") + scale_fill_viridis(discrete = T, option = "E") +
    ggtitle("Studying 4 species.") + facet_wrap(~specie) +
    theme_ipsum() + theme(legend.position="none") + xlab("")
